Video & Image App – Fully Decoupled + MVP Mocks

Three separate flows

Image (1 step)  





Step 1: Generate Image Links – Prompt (context + project + marketing) → output = image asset links.

Video (2 steps)  





Step 1: Generate Storyboard – Prompt → output = storyboard.  



Step 2: Generate Video from Storyboard – Storyboard → output = video asset links.

Upload (1 step)  





Step 1: Upload Assets – Choose assets from pool + choose platform(s) → save mapping.

Asset pool = all asset links: both image links (image_generation_assets.asset_url) and video links (video_generation_assets.asset_url). Upload treats them the same (choose any assets, map to platforms).



MVP: mock data (replace with real later)

Mock image links  





When user completes “Generate Image Links”, do not call any AI.  



Create image_generation + N image_generation_assets rows and set each asset_url to a mock link (e.g. placeholder image URL, or deterministic mock like https://picsum.photos/seed/{generation_id}_{index} or a fixed placeholder).  



Later: replace this with real API that returns image links.

Mock storyboards  





When user completes “Generate Storyboard” (Video Step 1), do not call any AI.  



Create/update video_generation_storyboards.content with mock storyboard data (e.g. default JSON: { "frames": [ { "scene": "Scene 1", "description": "..." }, ... ] } or a few sample frames).  



Later: replace with real storyboard generation.

Video links (mock for MVP)  





When user runs “Generate Video from Storyboard” (Video Step 2), do not call any AI.  



Set video_generation_assets.asset_url to mock video links (e.g. placeholder video URL or sample mp4).  



Later: replace with real video-from-storyboard API.

So in MVP the asset pool is populated with: mock image links + mock video links. Upload step lists all of them (with optional filter, e.g. last hour) and user chooses assets + platforms.



