Data model (unchanged)





image_generation_assets – asset_url (mock or real image link).  



video_generation_assets – asset_url (mock or real video link).  



video_generation_storyboards – content (mock or real storyboard jsonb).  



Upload reads from both asset tables; asset pool = union of all rows with asset_url (and optional time filter).



Implementation notes





Image flow: On submit, create generation + N asset rows; fill asset_url with mock image URLs (e.g. picsum or static placeholder).  



Video Step 1: On submit, create video_generation + storyboard row with mock content; editor can load/edit it.  



Video Step 2: “Generate Video” button creates/updates video_generation_assets and sets asset_url to mock video URLs.  



Upload: Query image_generation_assets and video_generation_assets (filter by created_at if needed); display as one list of “asset links”; user selects and maps to platforms.  



Later: swap mock generators for real AI/API; schema and flows stay the same.



